121
00:04:59,780 --> 00:05:01,360
He's got no public traces.

122
00:05:01,630 --> 00:05:03,190
I did find him logged as a patient

123
00:05:03,190 --> 00:05:05,230
at more than a dozen rehabs, though.

124
00:05:05,310 --> 00:05:07,030
Yeah, his school records are a mess.

125
00:05:07,030 --> 00:05:08,790
I mean, this kid's been in and out of a different school

126
00:05:08,790 --> 00:05:10,520
every year since he was 14.

127
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:13,780
So we think Braddem kicked him out of the house?

128
00:05:14,460 --> 00:05:16,280
Yeah, I mean, that would be my guess.

129
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:18,560
I can't figure out his relationship to Isla, though.

130
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:20,910
Friends, boyfriend, maybe they just use together?

131
00:05:20,910 --> 00:05:22,920
I'm scouring social media--

132
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:26,190
She's been waiting for you for over an hour.

133
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:28,290
We're halfway to that being her permanent office,

134
00:05:28,290 --> 00:05:29,550
so could you, please?

135
00:05:31,020 --> 00:05:32,020
Yeah, I'm back.

136
00:05:35,060 --> 00:05:35,900
Deputy.

137
00:05:36,030 --> 00:05:37,820
Have you got any baking soda in your office?

138
00:05:38,460 --> 00:05:39,550
I don't.

139
00:05:40,230 --> 00:05:43,080
- One of those stain pens? - Sorry.

140
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:44,130
That's a shame.

141
00:05:44,130 --> 00:05:45,650
I read your crime scene report--

142
00:05:45,650 --> 00:05:47,510
You wanna know if I know the Alderman?

143
00:05:47,510 --> 00:05:49,660
I'm just guessing where this is headed.

144
00:05:50,430 --> 00:05:53,040
The answer's no, I've never met Alderman Braddem.

145
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:55,770
Okay, because this is one of those instances

146
00:05:55,770 --> 00:05:58,620
