00:06:28,900 --> 00:06:29,960
Asap.

161
00:06:31,510 --> 00:06:34,640
You know, we don't have to go 12 rounds every time.

162
00:06:34,740 --> 00:06:36,230
I'm gonna give you an order. That's my job.

163
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:37,510
But we can be nice.

164
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:38,580
Can you see this?

165
00:06:40,390 --> 00:06:41,220
I can.

166
00:06:41,470 --> 00:06:42,560
Is it see-through?

167
00:06:43,700 --> 00:06:44,520
It is.

168
00:06:46,100 --> 00:06:48,280
Okay. Deputy Miller.

169
00:06:52,950 --> 00:06:53,840
Hey, Billy.

170
00:06:54,210 --> 00:06:55,340
Billy, look at me.

171
00:06:56,860 --> 00:06:57,870
Look at me.

172
00:06:57,870 --> 00:07:00,380
I'm Sergeant Hank Voight with the CPD.

173
00:07:00,510 --> 00:07:01,680
Hey, Billy.

174
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:03,800
Do you remember me? We were just downstairs.

175
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,020
We just talked.

176
00:07:07,540 --> 00:07:09,820
Boy, this kid's got no short-term memory whatsoever.

177
00:07:09,820 --> 00:07:11,620
I don't even think he knows where he is.

178
00:07:11,620 --> 00:07:13,600
Billy, do you know why you're here?

179
00:07:13,730 --> 00:07:14,670
Isla?

180
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:17,500
- Where is she? - She's dead.

181
00:07:17,940 --> 00:07:19,570
Can you tell us what happened to her?

182
00:07:21,610 --> 00:07:22,920
Hey, Billy.

183
00:07:23,540 --> 00:07:24,320
Billy!

184
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:27,350
The way we found you with the knife,

185
00:07:28,090 --> 00:07:30,700
this is a bad situation, do you understand?

186
00:07:31,740 --> 00:07:33,910
- Do you think I killed her? - I do.

187
00:07:33,950 --> 00:07:35,180
All right, this death looks like

188
00:07:35,180 --> 00:07:37,430
what we call a crime of passion, Billy.

189
00:07:37,660 --> 00:07:40,020
Like a fight broke out, something went wrong,

190
00:07:40,260 --> 00:07:41,890
a knife was grabbed from the kitchen.

191
00:07:41,890 --> 00:07:44,510
I didn't kill her. The--the man killed her.

192
00:07:44,520 --> 00:07:46,330
Okay, the man. What man?

193
00:07:46,390 --> 00:07:48,890
The man in the apartment. He killed her.

194
00:07:49,140 --> 00:07:51,540
- Who was he? - I don't know.

195
00:07:52,730 --> 00:07:54,440
Can you describe what he looked like?

196
00:07:55,450 --> 00:07:56,750
He was white.

197
00:07:57,240 --> 00:08:01,170
He was in his 40s. He...had green eyes.

198
00:08:01,870 --> 00:08:05,070
He was wearing a suit. White shirt.

199
00:08:05,470 --> 00:08:07,630
Blue tie with red stripes on it.

200
00:08:08,210 --> 00:08:09,960
He had this voice like...

201
00:08:10,210 --> 00:08:13,060
It was really light.

202
00:08:13,310 --> 00:08:15,820
And like he was telling a story.

203
00:08:15,820 --> 00:08:19,170
Like he knew what he wanted to say, and...

204
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,720
You ever seen this man before?

205
00:08:24,270 --> 00:08:25,570
Can I see Isla?

206
00:08:25,980 --> 00:08:27,130
She's dead, Billy.

207
00:08:32,210 --> 00:08:33,770
I just wanna see her again.

208
00:08:34,310 --> 00:08:35,650
Please, just...

209
00:08:36,710 --> 00:08:38,180
tell me where you put her.

210
00:08:43,700 --> 00:08:46,080
You ever hear a suspect description that detailed?

211
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:48,950
No. Maybe it's the high talking.

212
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,470
That detailed?

213
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:52,120
Or telling his own story.

214
00:08:52,580 --> 00:08:54,250
I just feel like you gotta be some amount of "Here"

215
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:56,070
to come up with that, and whether it's true or not,

216
00:08:56,070 --> 00:08:57,620
it seems like he believes it.

217
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:58,940
And he asked to see the body.

218
00:08:58,940 --> 00:09:00,790
That's not normal offender behavior.

219
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:01,640
Addicts' behavior doesn't always

220
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:02,980
match their truth, though.

221
00:09:02,980 --> 00:09:04,180
They know how to lie.

222
00:09:04,180 --> 00:09:06,590
I suppose he could be feeding us a fake suspect.

223
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:07,780
I don't know.

224
00:09:07,940 --> 00:09:10,560
And we're not gonna know more until he's sober.

225
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:13,050
Well, he gave us another suspect.

226
00:09:13,050 --> 00:09:14,070
Let's run it.

227
00:09:14,330 --> 00:09:15,810
You really wanna wait to charge?

228
00:09:15,810 --> 00:09:17,670
Until we know he's guilty, yeah.

229
00:09:28,700 --> 00:09:30,250
There's really nothing that would indicate

