558
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:15,510
I-I feel like I'm losing my mind.

559
00:23:15,510 --> 00:23:17,800
I know, but this is where you fight, okay?

560
00:23:17,930 --> 00:23:19,540
This is where you fight, okay?

561
00:23:22,690 --> 00:23:24,880
Okay? All right, all right, all right.

562
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:28,340
Now, you don't know Hadley. That's fine.

563
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:30,850
What about the drugs?

564
00:23:31,250 --> 00:23:32,560
What about the heroin?

565
00:23:33,810 --> 00:23:35,510
- The tag. - Okay.

566
00:23:35,610 --> 00:23:37,920
- The tag. - The insignia?

567
00:23:38,250 --> 00:23:40,180
- Yeah. - Okay, what about it?

568
00:23:40,250 --> 00:23:40,970
Yeah.

569
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:44,360
These bags of dope, they were in the black bag.

570
00:23:44,440 --> 00:23:45,910
She had a lot of them.

571
00:23:46,150 --> 00:23:48,010
Wait, you're saying that she had

572
00:23:48,030 --> 00:23:49,710
more than just a few grams?

573
00:23:49,710 --> 00:23:52,300
Yeah, the black bag was full of these bags.

574
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:58,860
Guys, I made a connection. Check this out.

575
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:01,850
This is Tim Rollins. He's 36 years old.

576
00:24:01,850 --> 00:24:04,600
He's got a history of violence, two priors for drug possession

577
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:06,440
with intent to distribute in Indiana.

578
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:09,090
Now, Hadley has calls, Venmo requests,

579
00:24:09,090 --> 00:24:10,570
and social media hits with this guy.

580
00:24:10,570 --> 00:24:11,930
So does Isla.

581
00:24:13,050 --> 00:24:14,650
And her social media is loaded with pictures

582
00:24:14,650 --> 00:24:16,860
of the two of them right up until when she met Billy.

583
00:24:17,660 --> 00:24:20,350
Ex-boyfriend. The drugs are definitely his.

584
00:24:20,350 --> 00:24:21,740
Isla knew it. She was itching.

585
00:24:21,740 --> 00:24:23,610
She went back. She stole the drugs.

586
00:24:24,120 --> 00:24:25,230
Bring him in.

587
00:24:34,660 --> 00:24:35,900
Blue Sedan.

588
00:24:46,590 --> 00:24:48,670
It's been cleaned. Bleach.

589
00:24:49,350 --> 00:24:50,500
Jay, Hailey.

590
00:24:50,830 --> 00:24:52,170
We dropped an anchor on Tim's place.

591
00:24:52,170 --> 00:24:54,240
We got a blue Sedan freshly scrubbed down.

592
00:24:54,240 --> 00:24:55,610
It's the exact match to the car

593
00:24:55,610 --> 00:24:57,180
idling outside Isla's apartment.

594
00:24:57,180 --> 00:24:58,840
Copy that. We're nine minutes out.

595
00:24:58,850 --> 00:25:00,570
We'll hold anchor until you arrive.

596
00:25:05,220 --> 00:25:06,350
Tim Rollins.

597
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:11,820
Stop!

598
00:25:11,820 --> 00:25:12,860
Chicago PD!

599
00:25:12,860 --> 00:25:14,390
- I'ma go around the back! - Copy.

600
00:25:20,460 --> 00:25:24,210
5021 Ida in foot pursuit. Westbound alley towards Bell.

601
00:25:24,430 --> 00:25:27,270
Offender is male, white. 6'2" in blue jeans.

602
00:25:27,280 --> 00:25:29,280
I need patrol cars off Bell and Waveland.

603
00:25:29,280 --> 00:25:30,970
I need containment right now.

604
00:25:32,790 --> 00:25:34,300
Copy that, 5021 Ida.

605
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:36,060
We will send units in your area.

606
00:25:36,060 --> 00:25:38,870
5021 Ida, I need an ETA on that backup!

607
00:25:40,270 --> 00:25:42,080
- Watch out! - 5021 Ida,

608
00:25:42,080 --> 00:25:43,500
units not responding.

609
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:47,000
Do I have containment or not? Where is everyone?

610
00:25:47,500 --> 00:25:49,290
Negative. No one in route.

611
00:25:54,330 --> 00:25:57,010
Dispatch, do I have cars coming? Where the hell is my backup?

612
00:25:57,380 --> 00:25:58,390
I lost eyes.

613
00:26:00,900 --> 00:26:01,740
Adam!

614
00:26:04,830 --> 00:26:05,750
Adam!

615
00:26:08,910 --> 00:26:10,790
Adam? 5021, 10-1. 10-1,

616
00:26:10,790 --> 00:26:12,320
shots fired. Officer down.

617
00:26:12,370 --> 00:26:14,470
Roll an ambo to the west alley of Bell.

618
00:26:14,470 --> 00:26:15,390
Where is he? Where is he? Where is he?

619
00:26:15,390 --> 00:26:16,800
He's gone, he's gone.

620
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:17,480
You--let me get this off.

621
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:18,160
Ah, I'm good, I'm good.

622
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:19,570
Shut up. You don't know that.

623
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:22,490
- It didn't go through. - I know.

624
00:26:22,500 --> 00:26:23,820
Rollins kept going. You should go.

625
00:26:23,820 --> 00:26:24,730
No, no, it hit your rib.

626
00:26:24,730 --> 00:26:25,860
You breathing all right?

627
00:26:26,230 --> 00:26:27,870
I'm fine. The wind's just knocked--

628
00:26:27,870 --> 00:26:28,730
Ruzek, where you at?

629
00:26:28,730 --> 00:26:30,380
It's good, bro. The vest took it.

630
00:26:30,380 --> 00:26:32,470
- What the hell happened? - Hit the ribs.

631
00:26:32,940 --> 00:26:34,900
I shouldn't have taken the corner.

632
00:26:34,970 --> 00:26:37,690
- Patrol never rolled. - He's good.

633
00:26:40,780 --> 00:26:43,030
They're not rolling with me. I'm sorry, bro.

634
00:26:43,040 --> 00:26:44,150
- It's all right. - I'm good.

635
00:26:44,150 --> 00:26:45,340
He's good.

636
00:26:45,580 --> 00:26:47,060
No, you just got shot 'cause of me.

637
00:26:47,060 --> 00:26:48,920
It's not on you, Kev. You're good.

638
00:26:48,920 --> 00:26:51,540
He just got shot. He just got shot.

639
00:26:56,220 --> 00:26:57,540
- Who didn't respond? - Kevin.

640
00:26:57,550 --> 00:26:59,020
I know it's on your radar.

641
00:26:59,060 --> 00:27:02,250
- Who didn't respond to the call? - Kevin, I am looking into it.

642
00:27:02,250 --> 00:27:04,500
I'm going to question every officer--

643
00:27:04,500 --> 00:27:05,550
Who was it?

644
00:27:07,250 --> 00:27:10,340
There were three patrol officers in the area and four tact guys.

645
00:27:10,340 --> 00:27:11,580
Who were the tact guys?

646
00:27:12,160 --> 00:27:15,130
Right now, every one of them has plausible deniability--

647
00:27:15,130 --> 00:27:17,110
Of course they do. Who were the tact guys?

648
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:21,350
McKenzie was one of them. Kevin, come on.

649
00:27:21,350 --> 00:27:23,200
Kevin, no. Kevin, please...

650
00:27:30,430 --> 00:27:31,270
Really?

651
00:27:31,730 --> 00:27:34,350
This is what we're doing? Letting cops get killed?

652
00:27:34,360 --> 00:27:36,820
- I was making an arrest. - Ruzek got shot.

653
00:27:36,820 --> 00:27:38,970
I couldn't roll on a call. Back the hell up, man!

654
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:40,590
You feel good, huh?

655
00:27:41,080 --> 00:27:42,750
Coming at good cops 'cause I told the truth?

656
00:27:42,750 --> 00:27:43,890
I'm not coming for you.

657
00:27:43,890 --> 00:27:45,480
You just wanna watch officers bleed out in the dirt--

658
00:27:45,480 --> 00:27:48,710
- I said I ain't coming-- - Yeah, you woke now?

659
00:27:48,780 --> 00:27:50,830
I gave you your answer. Now back up!

660
00:27:50,830 --> 00:27:52,740
I ain't backing no damn where, coward.

661
00:27:56,510 --> 00:27:58,580
You're still protecting your racist ass buddy?

662
00:27:58,580 --> 00:27:59,950
Not here, man.

663
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:02,240
You take a breath. It's us.

664
00:28:02,360 --> 00:28:04,530
- Take a breath. - He's giving orders.

665
00:28:07,890 --> 00:28:08,930
I'm good.

666
00:28:08,930 --> 00:28:10,810
You think any of us wanna be doing this?

667
00:28:11,300 --> 00:28:12,810
The world of police is burning down.

668
00:28:12,810 --> 00:28:14,370
You think patrol cops wanna be coming for you,

669
00:28:14,380 --> 00:28:15,750
risking their jobs?

670
00:28:17,680 --> 00:28:19,560
He's giving orders.

671
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:23,830
We got a lead on Rollins. We gotta go.

672
00:28:25,320 --> 00:28:26,850
I know you feel it.

673
00:28:27,740 --> 00:28:28,870
Nolan's still got the department.

674
00:28:28,870 --> 00:28:30,840
You'll never see them, never prove it.

675
00:28:30,840 --> 00:28:31,750
This is how they do it.

676
00:28:31,750 --> 00:28:33,470
They make you scared of your own shadow.

677
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:36,520
This is how they break you.

678
00:28:42,080 --> 00:28:44,130
We got Rollins entering the Wilson CTA stop

679
00:28:44,130 --> 00:28:45,910
two minutes after your 10-1 call, Ruz,

680
00:28:45,920 --> 00:28:47,660
and then exiting again at Belmont.

681
00:28:47,660 --> 00:28:49,870
Rollins has a cousin that lives two blocks from Belmont.

682
00:28:49,870 --> 00:28:51,330
Great place to hide out.

683
00:28:51,330 --> 00:28:52,630
Hey, Adam.

684
00:28:53,340 --> 00:28:55,730
- You okay? - I'm good.

685
00:28:55,850 --> 00:28:58,970
All right, we are not relying on Patrol this time.

686
00:28:59,310 --> 00:29:00,550
We secure the location

687
00:29:00,550 --> 00:29:03,170
and contain the perimeter ourselves, understood?

688
00:29:03,640 --> 00:29:05,300
- Let's do it. - Let's go.

689
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:14,550
Come on. Let's go.

690
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:38,670
- Back's secure. - Copy.

691
00:29:40,230 --> 00:29:42,000
Tim Rollins, Chicago PD. We have a warrant to enter.

692
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:43,770
I've got movement in the house--go.

693
00:29:46,480 --> 00:29:48,180
Kev, Adam, he's heading your way.

694
00:29:54,380 --> 00:29:55,500
- Stay down! - Stay there!

695
00:29:55,500 --> 00:29:57,370
Yeah, yes, stay down.

696
00:29:58,470 --> 00:29:59,710
Offender in custody.

697
00:30:01,220 --> 00:30:02,210
Confirm, Hailey.

698
00:30:02,210 --> 00:30:03,350
We got you. We got you.

699
00:30:03,350 --> 00:30:05,100
- Okay. - All right, let's go.

700
00:30:05,110 --> 00:30:06,950
Let's go. Get him up, get him up.

701
00:30:08,710 --> 00:30:09,930
This the gun you shot my partner with?

702
00:30:09,930 --> 00:30:11,380
- Get up. - Get him up.

703
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:13,160
Let's go.

704
00:30:20,680 --> 00:30:21,830
I'm sorry, bro.

705
00:30:22,940 --> 00:30:24,590
You got no reason to be sorry.

706
00:30:26,030 --> 00:30:27,870
You do know I got you, though, right?

707
00:30:28,580 --> 00:30:29,610
We all do.

708
00:30:30,850 --> 00:30:31,980
You're not alone.

709
00:30:50,510 --> 00:30:51,940
Yeah, I'm 10 minutes out.

710
00:30:53,180 --> 00:30:55,950
Hey, if you want me, then come get me.

711
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:57,050
I could take whatever you got.

712
00:30:57,050 --> 00:30:58,250
Not sure what you're talking about.

713
00:30:58,250 --> 00:31:00,180
Well, come for me, not my unit,

714
00:31:00,180 --> 00:31:02,180
good cops that don't got nothing to do with this.

715
00:31:02,180 --> 00:31:04,110
If I'm the one you want, then come for me!

716
00:31:05,010 --> 00:31:06,670
You know I did the right thing!

717
00:31:08,790 --> 00:31:10,140
"The right thing"?

718
00:31:10,950 --> 00:31:12,770
Is that what you think you did?

719
00:31:13,470 --> 00:31:15,940
You're the hero who crumpled the Blue Wall?

720
00:31:15,940 --> 00:31:18,610
Doyle was a gladiator cop that killed--

721
00:31:18,620 --> 00:31:20,310
Doyle was a dead man!

722
00:31:20,740 --> 00:31:23,430
He was already killed, and then you killed him again.

723
00:31:24,820 --> 00:31:27,370
You left his children with a dead father

724
00:31:27,370 --> 00:31:30,720
they gotta be ashamed of, and for what?

725
00:31:30,720 --> 00:31:32,990
You're standing exactly where you were.

726
00:31:33,510 --> 00:31:36,280
Blue Wall's still all around you.

727
00:31:38,190 --> 00:31:40,230
I'm gonna keep coming for you

728
00:31:41,620 --> 00:31:43,510
in any way I want

729
00:31:44,710 --> 00:31:46,970
until I have your badge.

730
00:31:59,040 --> 00:32:00,150
Evening.

731
00:32:01,010 --> 00:32:02,510
Heard you closed the case.

732
00:32:03,700 --> 00:32:04,860
Congrats.

733
00:32:06,260 --> 00:32:07,300
Really?

734
00:32:07,900 --> 00:32:09,480
It's professional courtesy.

735
00:32:11,570 --> 00:32:13,550
All right, I read it in the management book.

736
00:32:13,550 --> 00:32:15,120
It's supposed to build trust.

737
00:32:16,880 --> 00:32:18,220
Do you like me now?

738
00:32:19,630 --> 00:32:22,250
Look, I know you didn't get me 48 and protection for free.

739
00:32:22,250 --> 00:32:23,310
Can we just cut to the part

740
00:32:23,310 --> 00:32:24,760
where you tell me what you want?

741
00:32:24,760 --> 00:32:27,200
I gave you 48 because you were right.

742
00:32:27,790 --> 00:32:29,010
Look, I get it.

743
00:32:29,060 --> 00:32:31,430
You look at me, and you see everyone that came before me:

744
00:32:31,430 --> 00:32:32,970
Kelton, Woods, Brennan.

745
00:32:33,490 --> 00:32:35,810
You know their file is still up at Ivory?

746
00:32:36,220 --> 00:32:38,320
- They hated you. - They didn't hide it.

747
00:32:38,320 --> 00:32:40,580
- I'm not them. - They all said that too.

748
00:32:40,580 --> 00:32:43,360
I'm sure they did, but I'm just here to do a job,

749
00:32:44,310 --> 00:32:46,480
a job that I am very good at.

750
00:32:49,980 --> 00:32:51,740
I'm something new, Hank.

751
00:32:52,250 --> 00:32:54,020
Part of the new world, huh?

752
00:32:54,580 --> 00:32:55,680
Yeah.

753
00:32:57,140 --> 00:32:59,370
Chicago's an old city, Sam.

754
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:01,350
It is.

755
00:33:04,910 --> 00:33:07,280
You should get that. Go ahead.

756
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:09,550
Today was fun.

757
00:33:10,700 --> 00:33:12,790
The fight's always the good part.

758
00:33:12,790 --> 00:33:14,930
It's the only way you really see people.

759
00:33:20,350 --> 00:33:21,330
Voight.

760
00:33:39,650 --> 00:33:41,330
It's starting to get cold.

761
00:33:48,780 --> 00:33:50,620
Yeah, I know I got two options.

762
00:33:54,070 --> 00:33:57,070
Let you make some deal for me, or I hand over my badge.

763
00:33:58,880 --> 00:34:00,980
Well, I can't have you in my unit, Kev.

764
00:34:00,990 --> 00:34:02,300
- Not if-- - I know.

765
00:34:02,300 --> 00:34:04,190
Not if I'm jeopardizing cases.

766
00:34:04,450 --> 00:34:06,600
Or I'm risking team's lives. I get it.

767
00:34:07,020 --> 00:34:08,570
So let me help you.

768
00:34:13,020 --> 00:34:16,490
I already talked to Nolan. Listen.

769
00:34:21,580 --> 00:34:23,850
The deal would be I put a beef on your record.

770
00:34:23,850 --> 00:34:25,280
Official complaint.

771
00:34:25,620 --> 00:34:27,310
I mean, it would tie you down.

772
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:31,030
It means you'd never make detective,

773
00:34:31,030 --> 00:34:32,580
never leave my unit.

774
00:34:35,230 --> 00:34:36,380
It's a brick,

775
00:34:38,200 --> 00:34:40,320
but Nolan would stop coming--

776
00:34:40,320 --> 00:34:41,560
I'm not taking that.

777
00:34:41,560 --> 00:34:43,160
Then you're not gonna be a cop anymore.

778
00:34:43,160 --> 00:34:45,200
Maybe I don't wanna be a cop anymore.

779
00:34:47,040 --> 00:34:49,110
I'm constantly looking over my shoulder.

780
00:34:49,650 --> 00:34:50,780
I'm mad

781
00:34:51,410 --> 00:34:53,120
every hour, every minute, every second.

782
00:34:53,130 --> 00:34:55,880
I'm mad at Nolan, I'm mad at you, I'm mad at Ruzek.

783
00:34:56,690 --> 00:34:58,270
I'm mad at every white cop

784
00:34:58,560 --> 00:35:00,560
that feels like they can make a deal for me.

785
00:35:01,940 --> 00:35:04,290
And every cop that's done this job the wrong way,

786
00:35:04,290 --> 00:35:06,300
which means I'm mad at myself.

787
00:35:08,090 --> 00:35:09,090
I'm so mad, I don't even think

788
00:35:09,090 --> 00:35:10,250
I can do the job the right way anymore.

789
00:35:10,250 --> 00:35:12,090
Then do it different.

790
00:35:13,820 --> 00:35:14,730
Do it different.

791
00:35:14,730 --> 00:35:16,890
That's the win. You get to do it different.

792
00:35:16,890 --> 00:35:18,710
- And Nolan skates? - Nolan.

793
00:35:18,720 --> 00:35:23,060
Nolan, the way he polices, he's not gonna last another year.

794
00:35:23,060 --> 00:35:24,430
Then what's the point of giving him a damn thing?

795
00:35:24,430 --> 00:35:26,570
Because it's not a new world yet.

796
00:35:27,690 --> 00:35:29,170
It's just not.

797
00:35:29,230 --> 00:35:31,170
So we just wait for the whole world to change

798
00:35:31,170 --> 00:35:32,680
and just pull me up?

799
00:35:37,390 --> 00:35:38,550
What would you do?

800
00:35:40,240 --> 00:35:41,270
Voight?

801
00:35:43,280 --> 00:35:46,520
In my skin, with this world, would you do that?

802
00:35:46,950 --> 00:35:47,980
Me?

803
00:35:49,440 --> 00:35:50,440
No.

804
00:35:56,130 --> 00:35:58,260
I'd say you are a good cop.

805
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:01,470
And you're a good man, Kevin.

806
00:36:02,660 --> 00:36:05,470
And you ask me, as soon as you're not one anymore,

807
00:36:05,470 --> 00:36:06,720
they're winning.

808
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:15,210
Kevin, I...

809
00:36:17,460 --> 00:36:20,270
Listen, I'll back you no matter what you choose.

810
00:36:23,600 --> 00:36:26,110
But the question is, what do you wanna do?

811
00:36:59,460 --> 00:37:01,280
Nobody's home. I already checked.

812
00:37:02,180 --> 00:37:04,060
I wouldn't wanna scare your family.

813
00:37:04,290 --> 00:37:05,880
What the hell do you think you're doing?

814
00:37:05,880 --> 00:37:08,400
I'm a cop too. Nobody saw me come in.

815
00:37:15,620 --> 00:37:17,030
- You're gonna kill me? - No.

816
00:37:22,880 --> 00:37:24,600
I'm gonna tell you our way out.

817
00:37:24,630 --> 00:37:26,380
Well, that's not how this works.

818
00:37:26,380 --> 00:37:28,820
It is if I take the third option...

819
00:37:30,850 --> 00:37:33,080
where I give up my badge a different way.

820
00:37:34,650 --> 00:37:36,260
Where I sue you

821
00:37:37,450 --> 00:37:40,370
and I sue the Chicago Police Department...

